TopicTitle: How to compile into a dll when only given a limited source

Articles.Content:
Im trying to compile from source , but the contributor screwed up and only gave partial source and missing assemblies. It does come with a solution file and I can browse it just fine in VS. When I try to build I get over 5000 build errors stating pretty much all the code is "missing" and dependencies are not there when they are in fact there. Steps I did...

 

1. Load the .sln file in VS

2. Click build and/or debug

3. get 5000 errors

The scary thing is this is a github commit. That means other people trying to make a dll will have the same problems.
So you made sure that the project references points to KSP's dll and you have 5k errors ?

36 minutes ago, sarbian said:
